						Standard Motor Products (SMP) and Commercial Vehicle Group (CVGI) Critical Review					

June 24th, 2017  • 0 comments • Filed Under •
 by ABMN Staff



							Filed Under: Comparison Articles • Market News 






Tweet










Commercial Vehicle Group (NASDAQ: CVGI) and Standard Motor Products (NYSE:SMP) are both small-cap auto/tires/trucks companies, but which is the superior investment? We will contrast the two businesses based on the strength of their analyst recommendations, risk, valuation, dividends, earnings, profitabiliy and institutional ownership. 
Dividends


 Get Commercial Vehicle Group Inc. alerts:



Standard Motor Products pays an annual dividend of $0.76 per share and has a dividend yield of 1.5%. Commercial Vehicle Group does not pay a dividend. Standard Motor Products pays out 27.5% of its earnings in the form of a dividend. Standard Motor Products has raised its dividend for 6 consecutive years. 




Volatility and Risk
Commercial Vehicle Group has a beta of 0.63, suggesting that its share price is 37% less volatile than the S&P 500. Comparatively, Standard Motor Products has a beta of 1.81, suggesting that its share price is 81% more volatile than the S&P 500. 
